    <p>GPS CY­CLING COM­PUTER</p>
    <p>$899</p>
    <p>If you cy­cle to keep fit, check out the Garmin Edge 1030 Plus.</p>
    <p>This GPS cy­cling com­puter tracks rides, as well as pro­vides turn-by-turn nav­i­ga­tion, per­for­mance in­sights and train­ing guidance. Its Clim­bPro fea­ture lets you mon­i­tor the el­e­va­tion re­main­ing and grade for each climb when fol­low­ing a route or course. It has a 3.5-inch touch­screen dis­play, which Garmin claims will work even when it is wet or used with gloves.</p>

